    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-02-15T23:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-02-15T23:00:00-05:00" n="18"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d18">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.24/2–1648: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-02-16T12:00:00+08:00"
                            >February 16, 1948—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received February 16—9:44
                        a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>302. Note agreeing cancellation contract for automotive spare parts. (Embtel 278,
                    February 11, 6 p.m.) and requesting that $1,800,000 be returned to Chinese
                    Embassy Washington received. Note expresses hope that returned funds can be used
                    to acquire available surplus property on most favorable terms to be negotiated.
                    Text by airmail.<note n="41" xml:id="d18fn41">Not printed.</note>
                </p>
                <p>Sent Department 302, repeated Shanghai for OFLC as 129, February 16, noon.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stuart</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
